The paper deals with verification problems for autonomous swarms of mobile robots, which falls under the category of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA). The focus is on correctness proofs of algorithms, which involves logic and formal methods, making Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) another likely category. The robots are evolving in a discrete space with a finite number of locations, which can be modeled as a data structure, making Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) a possible category. The paper also discusses decision procedures and encoding in Presburger arithmetics formulae, which falls under Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) categories.
